# Introduction

## 

- Infectious disease testing  
  - Timely  
  - Efficient  

\pause
- COVID-19 pandemic  

\pause
- Group testing  
  - Also known as “pooled testing”  
  - Process in Nebraska (Abdalhamid et al. 2020)  

\pause
- Nebraska Governor Pete Ricketts press conference on March 24, 2020  

\pause
- Combine together portions of 5 specimens from different individuals into a “group”  

\pause
- Test as if it were a single specimen  
  - Group tests negative: All 5 individuals are negative  
  - Group tests positive: Retest each individual separately to determine who is positive or negative  
\pause
- Decrease number of tests, increase testing capacity  

## 

- Widely used during pandemic  
  - Universities (e.g., Duke and Cambridge), government-sponsored testing, healthcare workers, ...  
  - Government health organizations: US FDA and UK NHS  
  - News media: *The New York Times*, The Washington Post, ABC News, PBS Newshour, ...  

\pause
![](NYTimesJuly27-2020.png){fig-align="center" width=60%}

